Let’s do this together.
This is only the beginning.
And maybe, just maybe, you’ll find a little piece of yourself in my journey too.
Everyone told me to settle down. I chose to start over.
At 32, I left behind a stable job, a “perfect” life, and every plan society had written for me, just to ask myself one question: What if there’s more to life than this?

Scared? Yes.
Unprepared? Definitely.
But sometimes, you’ve got to jump before you’re ready. Because if you wait for the perfect moment, it might never come.

This series is not just about solo travel or quitting a job.
It’s about unlearning everything we were told about success, love, happiness, and timelines.
It’s about choosing courage over comfort—every single day.
It’s about figuring life out, one uncomfortable experience at a time.

If you’ve ever felt stuck, behind, or like you’re meant for something more…
Follow along.
You’re going to see every high, every low, and everything in between.

Mid Life Crisis 😝❤️ 
After 10 years of the corporate grind, I realized I needed more than just money in the bank. 🌟 Maybe my solution won’t fit your problem but this solution, to allow yourself to connect with your deeper self, have your freedom in your own hands, it needs you to be fearless. And trust that if you could do it once then you can do it again. Do the karma, let the fruit come whenever and even if it doesn’t come, koi na, Dekhi Jayagi Now, I’m embracing the unknown, chasing dreams, and living life on my own terms. 🚀 It’s scary, exciting, and liberating all at once. Here’s to new beginnings and the freedom to be whoever I want to be!!

Save this RARE & HIDDEN Thailand itinerary so unique, even frequent travelers haven’t heard of half these places.
It’s not just offbeat… it’s borderline secret. 👀

Forget touristy beaches and full moon parties —
This is Thailand like you’ve NEVER seen it before.

Here’s the full drop of places you won’t believe exist in one trip:

📍 Lalitta Café, Chiang Rai – A dreamy riverside café that feels like a Pinterest board
📍 Blue Temple, Chiang Rai – A glowing blue masterpiece, way less crowded than White Temple
📍 Sticky Waterfall, Chiang Mai – A waterfall you can literally climb barefoot!
📍 Long Neck Karen Village – A cultural walk into the lives of Thailand’s most iconic tribe
📍 Princess Lagoon, Krabi – Hidden between limestone cliffs; the hike is wild, the view is WILDER
📍 Flying Paramotor, Chiang Rai – You’re flying over rice fields, temples, and rivers. Unreal.
📍 Khompastr Cotton Factory, Hua Hin – Make your own butterfly print at Thailand’s first hand-printed textile studio
📍 Monsoon Valley Vineyard – Wine tasting with a view that rivals Tuscany

And the best part?
None of this is part of your usual Thailand itinerary.
It’s raw, peaceful, wild, and stupidly beautiful.

Honeyyy I want moneyyyy… but my OWN 🫶💪
They say “money can’t buy happiness”…
But let’s be emotionally intelligent for a sec.

Try finding inner peace on an empty stomach.
Try chasing your dreams without rent money.

Maslow had it right, before we self-actualize,
we need to survive, feel safe, stay connected, and feel worthy.
And guess what?
Money plays a role in every. single. layer.

✧ Food, shelter, safety
✧ Family dinners, flights home, late-night calls
✧ Therapy, hobbies, growth, freedom

So yeah, happiness is internal.
But money gives you the space to breathe.
To live life on your terms.
To stop settling.

Don’t let anyone glorify the hustle of struggle.
You deserve a soft life funded by hard work.
And babe, you can earn it all on your OWN. 💸❤️‍🔥

Tucked away at 14,100 ft in the Spiti Valley, Chandra Taal (literally Moon Lake) is one of India’s most surreal high-altitude lakes. The name comes from its crescent moon shape, and trust me, nothing prepares you for the magic of that first glimpse—the still blue waters, surrounded by snow-capped mountains, reflecting the sky like a dream. 🏔️✨

But getting here? That’s the real story. So if you’re planning a trip, here’s everything you need to know: 👇

🚘 ROUTE 1: Via Manali (Short but risky)
Manali → Atal Tunnel → Batal → Chandra Taal

Quickest route, but not recommended if you’re not acclimatized.
The altitude jump is too sudden, which can lead to AMS (Acute Mountain Sickness).
Only go this way if you’ve already spent a few days in the mountains.
🌄 ROUTE 2: Via Shimla-Kinnaur-Spiti (Longer but safer & scenic)
Delhi → Shimla → Kalpa → Nako → Tabo → Kaza → Chandra Taal

This route lets your body gradually acclimatize.
You also get to explore dreamy villages, monasteries, and maybe sip a buttery yak latte at a local café in Kaza before heading to the lake. ☕

🧳 What to pack:

Heavy winter jackets (even in June, nights go below zero)
Thermals, gloves, caps, woolen socks
Trekking shoes (trail is rocky)
Torchlight, power bank, dry snacks
Cash (no UPI, no network, no excuses)
💊 Medications to carry:

Diamox (helps prevent AMS, consult your doctor)
Dolo, ORS, Disprin
Inhaler if you’re prone to breathlessness
Altitude sickness can hit hard, so hydrate and go slow
🏕️ Where to stay:

Camps near Chandra Taal (basic, cold but unforgettable)
Book in advance during season (June to September)
🌙 When to go:

Best time: Mid-June to mid-October
After that, snow takes over and the roads shut down
This isn’t just a lake. It’s a feeling

We forgot to chase waterfalls.

Getting drenched under cold water, screaming with joy, slipping on wet rocks,

To play.

The world is busy promoting hustle.

Because fun is not a reward.

And this?

If this isn’t on your bucket list yet, you’re seriously missing out.
There’s one country where train journeys feel like magic, it’s Switzerland.
And these 6 rides? UNREAL. 👇

🥇 1. Glacier Express (Zermatt → St. Moritz)
8 hours of pure bliss. Panoramic windows, alpine villages, snowy peaks—feels like a moving luxury hotel.

🥈 2. Bernina Express (Chur → Tirano, Italy)
A UNESCO World Heritage route that takes you from glaciers to palm trees in just 4 hours.

🥉 3. GoldenPass Line (Lucerne → Interlaken → Montreux)
This is the reel-worthy route with wooden chalets, turquoise lakes, and dramatic mountain backdrops.

🏔️ 4. Voralpen Express (Lucerne → St. Gallen)
Perfect if you’re short on time but still want to soak in rolling hills, lakes, and forests.

🌸 5. Luzern–Interlaken Express
Think waterfalls, meadows, and storybook towns like Lungern—straight out of a fairytale.

🌿 6. Gornergrat Bahn (Zermatt → Gornergrat)
Switzerland’s highest open-air cogwheel railway! For the ultimate Matterhorn view—unmissable.

🎫 HOW TO DO THIS RIGHT (and on a budget!):
✅ Get the Swiss Travel Pass:

Gives unlimited travel on all public transport: trains, buses, boats (and most scenic trains too!)
Valid for 3, 4, 6, 8 or 15 days
Also includes 500+ museums, mountain excursions like Mt. Rigi & Stanserhorn, and boat rides!
No need to pre-book most journeys
🛒 Book here: www.sbb.ch/en or www.swiss-pass.ch

💸 Money Saving Tips
🍽️ Skip restaurants. Buy from supermarkets like Coop or Migros. Airbnb with a kitchen = game changer.
🚰 Tap water is drinkable everywhere. Carry a bottle.
🥾 Hike and picnic—it’s FREE and breathtaking.
📲 Book tours via HeadOut, Klook or GetYourGuide for discounts.
🛏️ Travel during shoulder seasons (April–May or Sept–Oct) to save on hotels.
🎟️ Book Glacier or Bernina Express seat reservations early (pass covers fare, not seat fee).

2 Days in Jaipur = 9 Iconic Stops 💗
Save this for your Pink City getaway!

🕌 Day 1: Heritage & Heights
📍 Panna Meena Kund – Hidden stepwell, zero crowd, 10/10 aesthetic
📍 Amber Fort – Sheesh Mahal + history = royal feels
📍 Jagat Shiromani Temple – Peaceful carvings & Meera Bai vibes
📍 Jal Mahal – Floating palace during golden hour = magic
📍 Padao, Nahargarh – Sunset + drink = chef’s kiss

🛍️ Day 2: Palaces, Shopping & Street Food
📍 Hawa Mahal – 953 windows of postcard perfection
📍 City Palace – Royal courtyards & THAT blue room
📍 Bapu Bazaar – Mojaris, jhumkas, bandhej galore
📍 Samrat + Lassiwala – Spicy kachori + legendary lassi = Jaipur joy
